Thanks Devaraj.

Just to be careful, can u pls confirm the following change doesn't break any of the MR CLI tests:

{noformat}
Index: hadoop-mapreduce-project/hadoop-mapreduce-client/hadoop-mapreduce-client-core/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/mapreduce/Job.java
===================================================================
--- hadoop-mapreduce-project/hadoop-mapreduce-client/hadoop-mapreduce-client-core/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/mapreduce/Job.java	(revision 1177158)
+++ hadoop-mapreduce-project/hadoop-mapreduce-client/hadoop-mapreduce-client-core/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/mapreduce/Job.java	(working copy)
@@ -462,8 +462,6 @@
     sb.append(status.getReduceProgress()).append("\n");
     sb.append("Job state: ");
     sb.append(status.getState()).append("\n");
-    sb.append("history URL: ");
-    sb.append(status.getHistoryFile()).append("\n");
     sb.append("retired: ").append(status.isRetired()).append("\n");
     sb.append("reason for failure: ").append(reasonforFailure);
     return sb.toString();
{noformat}

Also, shouldn't we do the check of amTrackingUrl v/s historyTrackingUrl in ClientServiceDelegate rather than in TypeConvertor.fromYarn? That way TypeConvertor is simple.
